# State Management & Data Layer

## Cubit (ViewModel) Pattern

Every feature flow has a paired Cubit + state file. Use **`Cubit`** only — never `Bloc<Event, State>`.

```
features/<feature>/view_model/<flow>/
├── <flow>_view_model.dart        # extends Cubit<FlowState>
└── <flow>_view_model_state.dart  # sealed/abstract state classes
```

```dart
// ✅ State file
abstract class LoginState extends Equatable {}
class LoginInitial extends LoginState { @override List<Object> get props => []; }
class LoginLoading extends LoginState { @override List<Object> get props => []; }
class LoginSuccess extends LoginState { ... }
class LoginFailure extends LoginState { final String error; ... }

// ✅ ViewModel
class LoginViewModel extends Cubit<LoginState> {
  final AuthRepository _repo;
  LoginViewModel(this._repo) : super(LoginInitial());

  Future<void> login(String email, String password) async {
    emit(LoginLoading());
    final result = await _repo.login(email, password);
    result.fold(
      (error) => emit(LoginFailure(error)),
      (data)  => emit(LoginSuccess(data)),
    );
  }
}
```

## BlocBuilder / BlocConsumer in Views

```dart
// ✅ GOOD — get Cubit from getIt, provide to tree
BlocProvider(
  create: (_) => getIt<LoginViewModel>(),
  child: BlocConsumer<LoginViewModel, LoginState>(
    listener: (context, state) {
      if (state is LoginFailure) showErrorSnackbar(context, state.error);
    },
    builder: (context, state) {
      if (state is LoginLoading) return const CircularProgressIndicator();
      return LoginForm();
    },
  ),
)
```

## Repository Pattern

Repositories live in `model/repositories/`. They call `DioHelper` and return either typed models or error strings.

```dart
class AuthRepository {
  final DioHelper _dio;
  AuthRepository(this._dio);

  Future<LoginResponse?> login(Map<String, dynamic> body) async {
    final response = await _dio.postData(endpoint: '/auth/login', data: body);
    if (response.statusCode == 200) {
      return LoginResponse.fromJson(response.data);
    }
    throw extractResponseError(response);
  }
}
```

## Networking — `DioHelper`

- Use `requiresAuth: true` in `Options.extra` to attach the Authorization header automatically.
- Convenience methods: `getData`, `postData`, `postFormData`, `putData`, `deleteData`.
- Error messages: use `extractResponseError(response)` from `dio_client.dart`.

```dart
// ✅ Authenticated request
final response = await _dio.getData(
  endpoint: '/seller/profile',
  options: Options(extra: {'requiresAuth': true}),
);
```

## App-wide Singletons

`AuthViewModel`, `ProfileViewModel`, `ThemeViewModel`, and `LocalizationViewModel` are registered as **singletons** and exposed via `MultiBlocProvider` in `main.dart`. Access them with `context.read<ThemeViewModel>()` anywhere in the tree.

All other Cubits are **factories** — instantiated fresh per screen via `BlocProvider(create: (_) => getIt<MyCubit>())`.
